Instructions

The first image is from before a catastrophic event and the second image is of the same location afterwards.

Compare the two images and answer all of the questions below to tell us about any damage to the property after the catastrophe.

Form can be submitted after answering Structure Visibility questions if remaining questions are unavailable.

Structure Visibility

Is there a structure generally centered and visible in both images?
(The top image was taken before a catastrophe, the bottom image afterwards.)
Does the imagery need to be recentered to better see the structure?
Are trees preventing you from properly assessing any damage at all to the structure?

Structure Damage

Are there any holes visible in the structure or any of its detached buildings?
Are there any tarps covering part of the structure or any of its detached buildings?
Has 10% or more of the total roof area been damaged (missing shingles, tiles, etc)?
Have any trees fallen onto the structure or any of its detached buildings?
Are there any branches on top the structure or any of its detached buildings?
(but not full trees)
Is there any other visible damage not covered by the previous questions?
Is any of the damage pre-existing? (The same damage exists in both images.)

Landscape & Debris

Is there visible pooling of water or evidence of a mudslide near the structure?
Are there any uprooted/downed trees on the property?
Have any non-structural objects been seriously damaged?
(for example: fence knocked down, deck or dock torn apart, etc)
Is 10% or more of the property's yard covered in debris?
Are there any pieces of debris that will require special equipment to move?
(for example: a boat, mobile home, flipped car, or other large item)

Review

Enter the date printed on the second image.

Please review your answers before submitting them.
